lse,"id":301022,"user_name":"江炜-律师","can_delete":false,"product_type":"c1","uid":1625580,"ip_address":"","ucode":"F0A9F8E1065858","user_header":"https://static001.geekbang.org/account/avatar/00/18/cd/ec/48f7ca3f.jpg","comment_is_top":false,"comment_ctime":1625486779,"is_pvip":false,"replies":[{"id":"109075","content":"这个比喻超棒","user_name":"作者回复","user_name_real":"高冷冷","uid":"2660210","ctime":1625568375,"ip_address":"","comment_id":301022,"utype":1}],"discussion_count":1,"race_medal":0,"score":"35985225147","product_id":100081501,"comment_content":"专注力，就像射箭。一定要有靶心，问题就是靶心。","like_count":9,"discussions":[{"author":{"id":2660210,"avatar":"https://static001.geekbang.org/account/avatar/00/28/97/72/794537fd.jpg","nickname":"高冷冷","note":"","ucode":"DC594DF2BAC858","race_medal":0,"user_type":2,"is_pvip":false},"reply_author":{"id":0,"avatar":"","nickname":"","note":"","ucode":"","race_medal":0,"user_type":1,"is_pvip":false},"discussion":{"id":522875,"discussion_content":"这个比喻超棒","likes_number":0,"is_delete":false,"is_hidden":false,"ctime":1625568375,"is_liked":false,"can_delete":false,"is_complain":false,"is_top":true,"parent_id":0,"ip_address":""},"score":2,"extra":"{\"reply\":true,\"user_type\":2}","child_discussion_number":0,"child_discussions":[]}]},{"had_liked":false,"id":299015,"user_name":"coder.js","can_delete":false,"product_type":"c1","uid":1338120,"ip_address":"","ucode":"3DE173A5D23690","user_header":"https://static001.geekbang.org/account/avatar/00/14/6b/08/15c473ef.jpg","comment_is_top":false,"comment_ctime":1624425383,"is_pvip":false,"discussion_count":0,"race_medal":0,"score":"23099261863","product_id":100081501,"comment_content":"个人笔记<br><br><br>Treisman 的研究显示，只有在“注意状态”下，我们才能做到对知识、概念、事物的透彻理解 和 学习。<br><br>## 心流<br><br>&gt; 心流：完全投入、十分专注于眼前行为 时的心理状态<br><br>“心流”会让我们从 忧虑感 和 压力中 解脱出来。<br><br>“心流”是我们获得幸福的一种途径。<br><br>提升专注力的第一个要点是“互动”。<br><br>### 🌰 例： 听课<br><br>听课是被动的，容易走神。<br><br>如何“互动”？<br><br>1. 边听，边默念老师的关键词。<br>2. 做笔记，但不能誊抄，而是有所取舍，有所整理，有所思考的记。<br><br>### 背书<br><br>1. 出声背<br>2. 用笔不时地写写划划<br><br>### 看书<br><br>1. 有选择地 划线 关键词<br>2. 稍加思考<br><br>思考和选择的过程，意味着你在主动参与。<br><br>&gt; 总之：做事的时候，不要让自己停留于“旁观者”的角色，要去主动进行“互动”，成为一个“参与者”。<br><br>## 带着问题<br><br>带着问题，问题使人专注。<br><br>比如：看悬疑片时候，会让人全神贯注。除了扣人心弦的剧情，还有一份“疑惑”。凶手是谁？会成功吗？<br><br>问题真的让人超级专注，带着困惑的大脑，总是会把认知资源（或者说注意力）留给寻求答案。<br><br>所以学习的时候，要学会提问：这段话可以回答什么问题呢？这个知识点，跟哪块儿知识有联系呢？<br><br>## 默念<br><br>考试如何集中？<br><br>何以解忧？<br><br>可以“默念”，“默念”在一定程度上还可以帮助你“超常发挥”。<br><br>**默念题目**，并且与**自己对话**：<br><br>- 这道题该选什么？<br>- 这是碳基生物能整出来的题？<br>- ~~今天晚上吃什么？~~<br><br>自我对话，都是不出声的，但一定要有口型。<br><br>吐槽和玩笑也会帮你缓解焦虑的情绪。<br><br>## 走神<br><br>走神本身并不是一个问题，你不需要自责。<br><br>走神了并意识到了，是训练专注力最为关键的部分。长此以往，你走神的次数会越来越少，而且发现走神、迅速回到学习状态的能力会越来越强。<br><br>所以你应该高兴，并且迅速恢复专注。<br><br>专注包含两块：<br><br>- 在若干时长，一直专注于一件事的能力<br>- 走神之后，重新让自己专注的能力<br><br>一直保持专注的能力，也是在“走神 - 重新专注 - 走神 - 重新专注”的过程中，训练得来。","like_count":5},{"had_liked":false,"id":298335,"user_name":"李沉舟","can_delete":false,"product_type":"c1","uid":1938141,"ip_address":"","ucode":"4212AE15278F2C","user_header":"https://static001.geekbang.org/account/avatar/00/1d/92/dd/ec53361b.jpg","comment_is_top":false,"comment_ctime":1624022038,"is_pvip":true,"replies":[{"id":"109021","content":"对的～","user_name":"作者回复","user_name_real":"高冷冷","uid":"2660210","ctime":1625461906,"ip_address":"","comment_id":298335,"utype":1}],"discussion_count":1,"race_medal":0,"score":"18803891222","product_id":100081501,"comment_content":"提升专注力，冥想很有用喔","like_count":4,"discussions":[{"author":{"id":2660210,"avatar":"https://static001.geekbang.org/account/avatar/00/28/97/72/794537fd.jpg","nickname":"高冷冷","note":"","ucode":"DC594DF2BAC858","race_medal":0,"user_type":2,"is_pvip":false},"reply_author":{"id":0,"avatar":"","nickname":"","note":"","ucode":"","race_medal":0,"user_type":1,"is_pvip":false},"discussion":{"id":522104,"discussion_content":"对的～","likes_number":0,"is_delete":false,"is_hidden":false,"ctime":1625461906,"is_liked":false,"can_delete":false,"is_complain":false,"is_top":true,"parent_id":0,"ip_address":""},"score":2,